---
/*
  DIY subpage 1 of 4 — How to Gather Participants (/diy/gather-participants).

  Sections, top to bottom (ticker, masthead, footer come from BaseLayout):
    1. Hero       — the M ❀ logo
    2. Heading    — cyan "* HOW TO GATHER PARTICIPANTS" bar
    3. Body       — the how-to copy, with a flyering photo mid-card
    4. Resources  — pink download cards (PDFs hosted on the site)
    5. Next       — link forward to the next subpage in the read-in-order set

  Underlined words in the body use plain <u> for emphasis (same as the home
  page's "offline.community"/"dumb.co") — they're not links.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import ResourceCard from '../../components/ResourceCard.astro';
import NextLink from '../../components/NextLink.astro';

// Download cards for the Resources section. The PDFs are uploaded later, so
// these hrefs 404 until the files land in /public/downloads/.
const resources = [
  {
    title: 'Month Offline Flyers',
    description: 'Editable posters that you can post around your neighborhood -- in 4 different colors! Include your phone number or e-mail address in the blank space at the bottom.',
    href: '/downloads/month-offline-flyers.pdf',
  },
  {
    title: 'Sign up form',
    description: 'Duplicate the interest form we created to keep track of all your participants.',
    href: '/downloads/month-offline-sign-up-form.pdf',
  },
  {
    title: 'Month Offline Postcards',
    description: 'Encouraging letters from past participants.',
    href: '/downloads/month-offline-postcards.pdf',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Gather Participants — Month Offline" masthead="Month Offline > DIY Guide > Participants">
  <div class="sections">
    <!-- 1. Hero -->
    <Hero />

    <!-- 2. Heading -->
    <SectionHeader label="How to gather participants" />

    <!-- 3. Body -->
    <section class="card">
      <p class="body">
        It's much easier to flip off in community than on your own. The first
        step is to <u>recruit</u> a group of 5-30 participants to go offline
        together. Invite some friends to join you, and ask them to invite some
        of their friends. Flyer on telephone boxes and in record stores, book
        shops, or cafes. Table on a busy street corner. Submit to local
        newsletters, magazines, and e-mail listservs. The world is your oyster!
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/mo_flyer.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="A hand wheat-pasting a Month Offline poster onto a city wall"
      />

      <p class="body">
        <u>Cold call</u> all the people who've signed up and get to know why
        they're joining, and what they hope to get out of the month. Set
        expectations and share a bit about yourself and your meetups.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        Create a <u>communication channel</u> like monthoffline@gmail.com or use
        an SMS service like Clicksend to keep participants in the loop. Send a
        <u>welcome postcard</u> in the mail to participants 1-2 weeks before your
        Month Offline begins.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Resources -->
    <SectionHeader label="Resources" />
    {resources.map((r) => (
      <ResourceCard title={r.title} description={r.description} href={r.href} />
    ))}

    <!-- 5. Next — read-in-order, per CLAUDE.md (Gather → Get Dumbphones → …). -->
    <NextLink label="How to Get Dumbphones" href="/diy/get-dumbphones" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Standard body paragraph (Syne Mono). Spacing between stacked paragraphs. */
  .body {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }
  .body + .body {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* The flyering photo sits between paragraphs inside the white card. */
  .card__photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }
</style>
